seriesStmt.title: Gregor Joseph Werner: A thematic catalogue of his works

annot.p: This work belongs to a group of five masses of which only the org part is extant. In contrast to the remaining works, however, three fugues of the present mass (Kyrie eleison, Cum Sancto Spiritu, and Osanna) also survive in the form of a short score comprising the chorus and continuo. The latter source was once owned by Joseph Haydn and is mentioned as no. 534 in his catalogue of artistic effects (“6. aus ſeinen Meſsen gezohene Fugen für die 4. Singſtimmen mit der Orgel für Komponisten”).

titlePage.p: Werner Joseph Gregor | 6 aus seinen Messen gezohene Fugen | für 4 Singstimmen mit Orgel.

annot.p: This source comprises six fugues and is mentioned in the catalogue of Joseph Haydn’s artistic effects (“6. aus ſeinen Meſsen gezohene Fugen für die 4. Singſtimmen mit der Orgel für Komponisten”). The present work is written on fol. 5r–6v and is the Kyrie eleison fugue (bars 93–130) from the Kyrie.
